---
// Submit a claim / label (CHK-4.2) — a reader can send a sleep claim or a product label that
// seems off. The SHELL is server-rendered and crawlable: how submissions are used (to prioritize
// research, feeding the correction process), and what we can and can't do with them. Only the
// form is an enhanced island (<ClaimSubmitForm/>), degrading to a plain POST with JS off.
//
// Framing (D4 + forbidden framings): we DESCRIBE how the queue works and route personal-health
// questions away — this is not a support desk, not medical advice, and never a place we tell
// someone what to take. Cross-links to /changelog (the correction process) and /label-checker.
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import ContextBanner from '../components/ContextBanner.astro';
import Disclaimer from '../components/Disclaimer.astro';
import ClaimSubmitForm from '../components/ClaimSubmitForm.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Submit a claim or label — help us prioritize what we research — Somnary"
  description="Found a sleep claim or a product label that seems off? Send it to Somnary. We read submissions to decide what to research and cover next — it feeds the public correction process. Not medical advice; we can't reply to everyone."
  canonical="https://somnary.vercel.app/submit-a-claim"
>
  <main class="page">
    <header class="head">
      <p class="eyebrow">Submit a claim or label</p>
      <h1 class="title">Send us a claim or label</h1>
      <p class="dek">
        Found a sleep claim or a product label that seems off? Send it and we’ll consider it for
        review. We read every submission to decide what to research and cover next — it’s one of
        the ways the tier board and the correction log stay honest.
      </p>
    </header>

    <ContextBanner
      note="This is how you flag something for us to look into — it isn’t a support channel or a place for a personal health question, and we can’t reply to everyone."
    />

    <div class="form-slot">
      <ClaimSubmitForm />
    </div>

    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="use-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">How we use it</p>
      <h2 id="use-heading" class="section-title">What happens to a submission</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Submissions go into a queue we read to <strong>prioritize what we research</strong>. A
          claim that keeps coming up, or a label that looks misleading, helps us decide which remedy
          or context page to write or revise next.
        </p>
        <p>
          If something you send reveals an error already on the site, it feeds the
          <strong>correction process</strong>: we log the change publicly on the
          <a href="/changelog">evidence change-log</a>, with what changed and when. We grade
          published human evidence — we don’t act on a single anecdote, and a submission never sets
          or changes a grade on its own.
        </p>
        <p>
          We can’t reply to everyone, and this isn’t medical advice. For anything about your own
          situation, talk to a pharmacist or clinician — start at the
          <a href="/safety">safety boundary</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="label-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Checking a label yourself</p>
      <h2 id="label-heading" class="section-title">Want to check a label first?</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          If you have the ingredients and amounts in hand, the free
          <a href="/label-checker">label checker</a> describes documented problems a panel can have
          — proprietary blends, doses outside the studied range, missing standardization — right in
          your browser. If it turns up something worth flagging, send it here.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="disclaimer-slot">
      <Disclaimer variant="standard" />
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .page {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--sp-8) var(--sp-7) var(--sp-9);
  }
  .eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-label);
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .head {
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-6);
  }
  .title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    line-height: var(--lh-3xl);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight);
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: var(--sp-3) 0 var(--sp-5);
  }
  .dek {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    line-height: var(--lh-md);
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: 68ch;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .form-slot {
    margin: var(--sp-6) 0 var(--sp-8);
  }

  .section {
    border-top: var(--border-hairline);
    padding-top: var(--sp-6);
    margin-top: var(--sp-8);
  }
  .section-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    line-height: var(--lh-xl);
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: var(--sp-2) 0 var(--sp-5);
  }
  .prose {
    max-width: 68ch;
  }
  .prose p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--lh-base);
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0 0 var(--sp-4);
  }
  .prose strong {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .prose a {
    color: var(--primary);
  }

  .disclaimer-slot {
    margin-top: var(--sp-8);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .page {
      padding: var(--sp-6) var(--sp-5) var(--sp-8);
    }
    .title {
      font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    }
  }
</style>
